org.cougaar.util.annotations
Annotation Type Cougaar.Predicate

Deprecated. 

@Retention(value=RUNTIME)
@Deprecated
public static @interface Cougaar.Predicate

Attaching this kind of annotation to a public method causes it to be used as a filter for an Cougaar.Execute method with a matching Cougaar.Execute.when(). A predicate method must be a public, must return a boolean and must take exactly one argument. Further, the type of the argument should match that of the one argument of the corresonding Cougaar.Execute. This annotation is deprecated. Instead of annotating a method this way, the preferred approach is simply to make the name a predicate method match the value of the Cougaar.Execute.when() clause.
